00:09:28.400 --> 00:09:29.460
and blowing some bubbles,

00:09:29.460 --> 00:09:30.980
and trying to light it off with that.

00:09:30.980 --> 00:09:32.480
It might work a little bit better.

00:09:32.480 --> 00:09:36.620
[Music]

00:09:36.620 --> 00:09:37.800
Yeah!

00:09:37.800 --> 00:09:41.140
[Music]

00:09:41.140 --> 00:09:43.120
But I think I'm getting
the hang of what does work.

00:09:43.120 --> 00:09:44.380
If I don't press down quite as much,

00:09:44.380 --> 00:09:46.740
letting out the butane in a slower stream,

00:09:46.740 --> 00:09:48.340
it doesn't pop the bubble as often,

00:09:48.340 --> 00:09:50.060
plus the pressure difference between

00:09:50.060 --> 00:09:52.220
inside the bubble and
outside the bubble is lower,

00:09:52.220 --> 00:09:54.430
so we get less air and more butane,

00:09:54.430 --> 00:09:55.820
which is more flammable.

00:09:55.820 --> 00:09:57.020
This is working okay.

00:09:57.020 --> 00:09:58.840
Actually, a little better
than I thought it would.

00:09:58.840 --> 00:10:00.580
But it's really hard to see in the daylight.

00:10:00.580 --> 00:10:02.020
I think we need to go to night.

00:10:02.520 --> 00:10:03.020
Okay.

00:10:03.020 --> 00:10:03.740
There we go. That's better.

00:10:03.740 --> 00:10:07.120
We should now be able to see
if things are actually lighting on fire.

00:10:07.120 --> 00:10:08.540
Let's give it another try.

